      <TR VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
        <TD HEIGHT=141 COLSPAN=5>
        </TD>
        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-10-30 - Direct X EverQuest Client Update</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p>The date for Direct X 7 is getting closer. For those of you running older
video drivers, be advised that the next EverQuest client patch will require
Direct X 7a. There are a lot of good things to say about this change. We have
been out on the test server exploring the updates and I have to say, things are
improved. First off, Gamma correction and MIP Mapping under a Direct X video
driver finally works. They have also done a lot of work on a new Sound Driver
for Sound Blaster Live users, which does a much better job of positional sound
effects. Although we noticed that the music tracks seem subdued to the the sound
and background noises, hopefully they are working on that.</p>
<p><font color="#0000FF">On the video side, look for:</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">1). Better performance, in general less skipping and
choppy sound.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">2). Gamma works, Yes!</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">3). MIP Mapping works for Direct X, About time!</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">4). Fogging works on some cards that it currently does
not, have to see about this one - we have not run into this problem.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">5). Full Screen Anti-Aliasing and alternate zbuffering
options will become avaliable. </font></p>
<p><font color="#0000FF">On the sound side:</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">1). Better performance, less choppy sound.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">2). Better positional audio (sound comes from where it
should).</font></p>
<p><font color="#FFFF00">3). Better sound balance (back effects no longer
override local sound and music).</font></p>
<p><font color="#0000FF">The down side:</font></p>
<p><font color="#FF0000">1). No direct X 7a and your S.O.L., so get those
updates.</font></p>
<p><font color="#FF0000">2). Old Video cards the do not support Direct X have to
be upgraded. </font></p>
<p>The patch is due in the &quot;next couple of weeks&quot; meaning early
November. Go to the Test Server and check it out now. That way you will be ready
for the big switch.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

